Sentencas: Effects of palladium (Pd) impregnation on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathodes are investigated with density functional theory plus U (DFT + U) and experimental methods.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: In-situ high temperature X-ray diffractometer results show that the impregnated Pd species exist at states of palladium oxide (PdO) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: The measured electrochemical impedance spectroscopy at 700 degrees C indicates PdO modification promotes the catalytic activity of LSCF cathodes.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: The modification structure of PdO on LSCF surfaces and effects of PdO modification on the performance of LSCF cathodes are investigated with DFT + U methods.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: The results show that B-8 with PdO molecule modification by a parallel posture on LSCF surface is the most stable structure.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: O-2 prefers to be adsorbed on AO-terminated surfaces rather than that on BO2-terminated ones.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: The oxygen surface adsorption activity of LSCF surface is improved by PdO modification.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: The calculated partial densities of states (PDOS) and Fermi level of O-2 adsorption on LSCF surfaces imply that the charge transfer is easier with PdO modification than that without PdO modification because PdO acts as a metal-like modification.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study

Sentencas: The PdO modification on LSCF surface leads to a better oxygen surface adsorption activity of LSCF cathodes.
Titulo: Effects of PdO modification on the performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells: A first principle study
